    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-10-10T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-10-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="525"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d525">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">894.404/10–1045: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Acting Political Adviser in Japan</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Atcheson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-10-10">October 10,
                            1945</date>.<lb/>[Received October 9 [<hi rend="italic">10?</hi>]—9:38
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>36. Press here carries sensational accounts of Vincent’s broadcast (ZA 6688)
                    October 7<note n="28" xml:id="d525fn1">For text of radio broadcast, see
                        Department of State <hi rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>, October 7, 1945, pp.
                        538–545.</note> in regard to abolition of Shintoism as Japanese state
                    religion. GHQ Information and Education Section is receiving numerous inquiries
                    as to details, etc., and it would be helpful if pertinent information could be
                    sent us by telegraph.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Atcheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
